Download Page for libeiskaltdcpp2.2_2.2.9-4+nmu3_amd64.deb

If you are running Debian, it is strongly suggested to use a package manager like aptitude or synaptic to download and install packages, instead of doing so manually via this website.

1. Add this line to your /etc/apt/sources.list :

deb http://notesalexp.org/debian/jessie/ jessie main

2. Fetch and install the GnuPG key

sudo aptitude update && sudo aptitude install notesalexp-keyring

sudo aptitude update

or

wget -O - http://notesalexp.org/debian/alexp_key.asc | sudo apt-key add -

sudo aptitude update

3. Enjoy

sudo aptitude install libeiskaltdcpp2.2

You can download the requested file from the pool/main/e/eiskaltdcpp subdirectory at this link:

http://notesalexp.org/jessie/main/e/eiskaltdcpp/libeiskaltdcpp2.2_2.2.9-4+nmu3_amd64.deb
